	<h1>Books &amp; CDs</h1>
		<div id="books">
		<h3>Books</h3>
		<p>Craobh Naithí have published a number of Tune books and 
		cds. They are intended to help students by providing a selection of tunes 
		which once learned enable the musician to play with others in our groups and bands
		as well as impromptu sessions. They are produced to the highest musical standards and are recommended.
		</p>
		<p><img alt="Book Two" height="250" src="App_Themes/Theme1/images/book_2.JPG" width="175" class="floatR"  /></p>
		<p><img src="App_Themes/Theme1/images/book_1.JPG" alt="Book One" class="floatR" /></p>
		<h3>Irish Traditional Music - Book One</h3>
		<p>A wide selection of tunes encompassing most of the rhythm types:- Reels; Double and Single Jigs;
		Slip Jigs; Hornpipes; Flings; Polkas; Marches; Airs; Christmas Tunes and the National Anthem.</p>
		<h3>Irish Traditional Music - Book Two</h3>
		<p>A further collection to expand the student’s repertoire. Both books were 
		compiled by Michael Tubridy and Edited by Méabh Ní Lochlainn, two highly respected musicians. </p>
		</div>
		<hr />
		<div id="cds">
	    <p><img src="App_Themes/Theme1/images/cdcover.jpg" alt="cd cover" class="floatL" /></p>
	    <p><img src="App_Themes/Theme1/images/covernew.jpg" alt="cd cover" class="floatL" /></p>
		<h3>CDs</h3>
		<h3>Book One</h3>
		<p><b>The ‘Yellow’ Book</b></p>
		<p>This 3-pack of CD's covers all 128 tunes in the Yellow Book, and includes a couple of extra tracks to help with instrument tuning. Most tunes are played slowly and then at session speed. This CD set should be of considerable help students of traditional Irish music, as it offers a
		unique chance to hear the tunes from the Yellow Book as they should be played.</p>
		</div>
		<div id="Book2">
		<h3>Book Two</h3>
		<p><b>The ‘Green’ Book</b></p>
		<p>A collection of 3 CD's which cover all the tunes in the Green book, most played slowly and then at regular tempo on fiddle, concertina, 
            accordion, flute, whistle and harp, or sung.</p>
